FAQ

Everything you need to know

What is a Managed Service Provider (MSP)?
A Managed Service Provider (MSP) is a company that remotely manages a customer's IT infrastructure and end-user systems. We provide proactive IT support, monitoring, and management to ensure your technology runs smoothly, allowing you to focus on your core business.
What type of businesses do you srve?
We serve a wide range of businesses, from small startups to medium-sized enterprises across various industries. Our services are scalable and can be tailored to meet the specific needs of your organization, regardless of its size or sector.
How can your services benefit my business?
Our services can benefit your business in several ways:

- Improved IT reliability and performance
- Enhanced cybersecurity
- Reduced downtime
- Cost-effective IT management
- Access to expert IT support
- Scalable solutions that grow with your business
- Freeing up your time to focus on core business activities
How long does it take to get started with your services?
We will get started within 24 hours of receiving your initial pay. Onboarding for each company and project will vary, but the process for each is similar in having your requirements as top priority.
How do w get started with your services?
Getting started is easy:

1) Contact us for an initial consultation.
2) We'll assess your current IT environment and needs.
3) We'll provide a customized proposal outlining recommended services and pricing.
4) Once you approve, we'll begin the onboarding process, including initial setup and staff training
